BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Choir Boy
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260806T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260806T214500
DTSTAMP:20260718T203507Z
UID:occ-54@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tarell Alvin McCraney's coming-of-age play about a gifted quee
 r student leading his prep school's gospel choir.\n\nTarell Alvin McCraney
 's coming-of-age drama\, threaded throughout with gospel spirituals. Pharu
 s\, the most gifted singer at an elite prep school devoted to raising youn
 g Black men into leaders\, wins the coveted post of choir lead\, and finds
  that being both talented and unmistakably himself puts him at odds with c
 lassmates and tradition alike. McCraney wrote the Oscar-winning film Moonl
 ight\, and this play reached Broadway in 2019 with a Tony nomination for B
 est Play. Presented by Actor's Express.
GEO:33.7817253;-84.4160629
LAST-MODIFIED:20260718T203442Z
LOCATION:King Plow Arts Center\, 887 W Marietta St NW\, Suite J-107
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://purchase.actors-express.com/EventAvailability?EventId=32601
END:VEVENT
