BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:i never asked for a gofundme
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261002T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261002T214500
DTSTAMP:20260718T203507Z
UID:occ-36@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:A world-premiere play: top surgery mistaken for breast cancer\
 , and a small-town GoFundMe nobody asked for.\n\nMillie and her partner Av
 ery are riding out Avery's recovery from gender-affirming top surgery in M
 illie's hometown of Mobile\, Alabama. Then a nosy evangelical family frien
 d misreads the surgery as a breast-cancer fight and launches a GoFundMe on
  the couple's behalf\, making them the talk of the town and the recipients
  of donations they never wanted. Whether to keep the money\, and what keep
 ing it would cost them\, is the question. A world premiere from Actor's Ex
 press.
GEO:33.7817253;-84.4160629
LAST-MODIFIED:20260718T203442Z
LOCATION:King Plow Arts Center\, 887 W Marietta St NW\, Suite J-107
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://purchase.actors-express.com/EventAvailability?EventId=32801
END:VEVENT
